    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-07T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="1405"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1405">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/8–745: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1405<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent—<gloss target="#t_Niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-07T22:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 7, 1945—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4769. <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> requested <persName
                        corresp="#p_BAE1">Bogomolov</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_CAD1">Duff
                        Cooper</persName> and myself to call this evening. He delivered to us six
                    identical notes containing the views of the French Govt on the decisions made at
                    Potsdam. The French Govt accepts in each case the decisions but formulates
                    various <pb facs="1751" n="1551" xml:id="pg_1551"/> “reservations”, “regrets”
                    and “observations”. (My 4722, Aug 6, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d1405fn1">
                        <ref target="#d1402">Document No. 1402</ref>.</note>)</p>
                <p>The texts of these six notes are being cabled in my six immediately following
                    telegrams.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
